subject: Remove override of createJSModules
body:
Since of recently in master the unused createJSModules has been removed and ReactPackage's no longer contain the definition of createJSModules. There for it must be removed in order to not yield a compile error. This is breaking change.

https://github.com/facebook/react-native/commit/ce6fb337a146e6f261f2afb564aa19363774a7a8

subject: Add prop-types as peer-dependency
body: This library currently depend implicitly on prop-types being installed and if it's not implicitly installed, then it fails. That's bad. We *need* to either add it as a dependency or a peerDependency. Please don't get this PR caught up in a bureaucratic clusterf#@%. I have no opinion on how this should be done. But it *needs* to be done.

subject: Fix flow issue in FBLoginButton
body:
The **onLoginFinished** was typed with a callback of type **LoginResultCallback** (therefore only one parameter), but **onLoginFinished** is used with two parameters at line 108.

There are two solutions to this problem.
The first is to change the call to line 108 in `this.props.onLoginFinished(eventDict)` instead of `this.props.onLoginFinished(eventDict.error, eventDict.result)`

The second is to change the typing of onLoginFinished (like in this pull request).

The first solution is breaking compatibility, the second solution isn't breaking compatibility

subject: Consolidate JS files under single `js/` directory.
body: There's little point to having lots of directories with just 1-2 files in them each. For bigger groups (in fbsdkshare) we can have subdirectories (e.g. `js/models`).

subject: Remove Haste-style providesModule declarations
body: They have no meaning in an npm package.

subject: Clean up coding style: - No need for an ES6 `class` if it only contains `static` methods. That's called a singleton object. - Declare Flow types for recurring types. Specify maps or the shape of objects instead of the indescript `Object` where possible. - Subsequently remove pointless `@typechecks`-style parameter annotations from the comments because they add no value beyond the Flow annotations and are just line noise - Add `.flowconfig` file below the Sample app since it pulls in all three libraries, so it's the best place to run `flow` in the standalone git repo. - Stick to 80 chars per line in JS

Refactor FBSDKAccessToken: - Fix name of date getters so it's clear they're getters and not properties (breaking API change!) - Make constructor take a dict rather than individual values. This'll make it easier to construct the token from other native callbacks, such as the login callback.
Refer to Linking Libraries guide in README for all the finicky Xcode setup bits
